But we know `x' ∈ (ker f)` because `f x' = 0`.
Therefore, `(Ideal.Quotient.mk (ker f)) x'` is the zero element of `R ⧸ (ker f)`.
But `(Ideal.Quotient.mk (ker f)) x'` is `x`.
So `x` is the zero element of `R ⧸ (ker f)`.
Therefore, `x = 0`.

So we need to show that `f x' = 0` implies `x = 0`.
We know `x = (Ideal.Quotient.mk (ker f)) x'`.
And `(Ideal.Quotient.mk (ker f)) x'` is `0` in `R ⧸ (ker f)` if and only if `x' ∈ (ker f)`.
But we know `x' ∈ (ker f)` because `f x' = 0`.
So `(Ideal.Quotient.mk (ker f)) x'` is `0`.
But `(Ideal.Quotient.mk (ker f)) x'` is `x` by `hx'`.
So `x = 0`.

